io.485. Epub 2010 Nov 21.\n\n# Prephenate aminotransferase directs plant phenylalanine biosynthesis via arogenate\n\n[Hiroshi Maeda](/?term=Maeda+H&cauthor_id=21102469)  [1](#full-view-affiliation-1 \"Department of Horticulture and Landscape Architecture, Purdue University, West Lafayette, Indiana, USA.\") , [Heejin Yoo](/?term=Yoo+H&cauthor_id=21102469), [Natalia Dudareva](/?term=Dudareva+N&cauthor_id=21102469)\n\nAffiliations Expand\n\n### Affiliation\n\n-   1 Department of Horticulture and Landscape Architecture, Purdue University, West Lafayette, Indiana, USA.\n\n-   PMID: **21102469**\n-   DOI: [10.1038/nchembio.485](https://doi.org/10.1038/nchembio.485)\n\nItem in Clipboard\n\n# Prephenate aminotransferase directs plant phenylalanine biosynthesis via arogenate\n\nHiroshi Maeda et al. Nat Chem Biol. 2011 Jan.\n\nShow details\n\nDisplay options\n\nDisplay options\n\nFormat Abstract PubMed PMID\n\nNat Chem Biol\n\nActions\n\n-   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Nat+Chem+Biol%22%5Bjour%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n-   [Search in NLM Catalog](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog?term=%22Nat+Chem+Biol%22%5BTitle+Abbreviation%5D)\n-   [Add to Search](#)\n\n. 2011 Jan;7(1):19-21.\n\ndoi: 10.1038/nchembio.485. Epub 2010 Nov 21.\n\n### Authors\n\n[Hiroshi Maeda](/?term=Maeda+H&cauthor_id=21102469)  [1](#short-view-affiliation-1 \"Department of Horticulture and Landscape Architecture, Purdue University, West Lafayette, Indiana, USA.\") , [Heejin Yoo](/?term=Yoo+H&cauthor_id=21102469), [Natalia Dudareva](/?term=Dudareva+N&cauthor_id=21102469)\n\n### Affiliation\n\n-   1 Department of Horticulture and Landscape Architecture, Purdue University, West Lafayette, Indiana, USA.\n\n-   PMID: **21102469**\n-   DOI: [10.1038/nchembio.485](https://doi.org/10.1038/nchembio.485)\n\nItem in Clipboard\n\nFull text links Cite\n\nDisplay options\n\nDisplay options\n\nFormat AbstractPubMedPMID\n\n## Abstract\n\nThe aromatic amino acids L-phenylalanine and L-tyrosine and their plant-derived natural products are essential in human and plant metabolism and physiology. Here we identified Petunia hybrida and Arabidopsis thaliana genes encoding prephenate aminotransferases (PPA-ATs), thus completing the identification of the genes involved in phenylalanine and tyrosine biosyntheses. Biochemical and genetic characterization of enzymes showed that PPA-AT directs carbon flux from prephenate toward arogenate, making the arogenate pathway predominant in plant phenylalanine biosynthesis.\n\n[PubMed Disclaimer](/disclaimer/)\n\n## References\n\n1.  1.  Annu Rev Plant Biol. 2003;54:519-46 - [PubMed](/14503002/)\n2.  1.  Phytochemistry. 2003 Mar;62(6):997-1008 - [PubMed](/12590126/)\n3.  1.  Plant Cell. 2008 May;20(5):1316-29 - [PubMed](/18487352/)\n4.  1.  J Bacteriol. 1979 Jun;138(3):805-15 - [PubMed](/457594/)\n5.  1.  Arch Biochem Biophys. 1985 Apr;238(1):237-46 - [PubMed](/3985619/)\n\nShow all 18 references\n\n## Publication types\n\n-   Research Support, Non-U.S. Gov't\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Research+Support%2C+Non-U.S.+Gov%27t%22%5Bpt%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Research+Support%2C+Non-U.S.+Gov%27t)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Research Support, U.S. Gov't, Non-P.H.S.\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Research+Support%2C+U.S.+Gov%27t%2C+Non-P.H.S.%22%5Bpt%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Research+Support%2C+U.S.+Gov%27t%2C+Non-P.H.S.)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n\n## MeSH terms\n\n-   Carbon Cycle / physiology\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Carbon+Cycle%2Fphysiology%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Carbon+Cycle)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Humans\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Humans%22%5BMeSH%5D&sor