m=%22FEBS+J%22%5BTitle+Abbreviation%5D)\n-   [Add to Search](#)\n\n. 2008 Oct;275(19):4824-35.\n\ndoi: 10.1111/j.1742-4658.2008.06621.x. Epub 2008 Aug 22.\n\n# A comparative biochemical and structural analysis of the intracellular chorismate mutase (Rv0948c) from Mycobacterium tuberculosis H(37)R(v) and the secreted chorismate mutase (y2828) from Yersinia pestis\n\n[Sook-Kyung Kim](/?term=Kim+SK&cauthor_id=18727669)  [1](#full-view-affiliation-1 \"National Institute of Standards and Technology, Gaithersburg, MD, USA.\") , [Sathyavelu K Reddy](/?term=Reddy+SK&cauthor_id=18727669), [Bryant C Nelson](/?term=Nelson+BC&cauthor_id=18727669), [Howard Robinson](/?term=Robinson+H&cauthor_id=18727669), [Prasad T Reddy](/?term=Reddy+PT&cauthor_id=18727669), [Jane E Ladner](/?term=Ladner+JE&cauthor_id=18727669)\n\nAffiliations Expand\n\n### Affiliation\n\n-   1 National Institute of Standards and Technology, Gaithersburg, MD, USA.\n\n-   PMID: **18727669**\n-   DOI: [10.1111/j.1742-4658.2008.06621.x](https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1742-4658.2008.06621.x)\n\nFree article\n\nItem in Clipboard\n\nComparative Study\n\n# A comparative biochemical and structural analysis of the intracellular chorismate mutase (Rv0948c) from Mycobacterium tuberculosis H(37)R(v) and the secreted chorismate mutase (y2828) from Yersinia pestis\n\nSook-Kyung Kim et al. FEBS J. 2008 Oct.\n\nFree article\n\nShow details\n\nDisplay options\n\nDisplay options\n\nFormat Abstract PubMed PMID\n\nFEBS J\n\nActions\n\n-   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22FEBS+J%22%5Bjour%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n-   [Search in NLM Catalog](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog?term=%22FEBS+J%22%5BTitle+Abbreviation%5D)\n-   [Add to Search](#)\n\n. 2008 Oct;275(19):4824-35.\n\ndoi: 10.1111/j.1742-4658.2008.06621.x. Epub 2008 Aug 22.\n\n### Authors\n\n[Sook-Kyung Kim](/?term=Kim+SK&cauthor_id=18727669)  [1](#short-view-affiliation-1 \"National Institute of Standards and Technology, Gaithersburg, MD, USA.\") , [Sathyavelu K Reddy](/?term=Reddy+SK&cauthor_id=18727669), [Bryant C Nelson](/?term=Nelson+BC&cauthor_id=18727669), [Howard Robinson](/?term=Robinson+H&cauthor_id=18727669), [Prasad T Reddy](/?term=Reddy+PT&cauthor_id=18727669), [Jane E Ladner](/?term=Ladner+JE&cauthor_id=18727669)\n\n### Affiliation\n\n-   1 National Institute of Standards and Technology, Gaithersburg, MD, USA.\n\n-   PMID: **18727669**\n-   DOI: [10.1111/j.1742-4658.2008.06621.x](https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1742-4658.2008.06621.x)\n\nItem in Clipboard\n\nFull text links Cite\n\nDisplay options\n\nDisplay options\n\nFormat AbstractPubMedPMID\n\n## Abstract\n\nThe Rv0948c gene from Mycobacterium tuberculosis H(37)R(v) encodes a 90 amino acid protein as the natural gene product with chorismate mutase (CM) activity. The protein, 90-MtCM, exhibits Michaelis-Menten kinetics with a k(cat) of 5.5+/-0.2s(-1) and a K(m) of 1500+/-100microm at 37 degrees C and pH7.5. The 2.0A X-ray structure shows that 90-MtCM is an all alpha-helical homodimer (Protein Data Bank ID: 2QBV) with the topology of Escherichia coli CM (EcCM), and that both protomers contribute to each catalytic site. Superimposition onto the structure of EcCM and the sequence alignment shows that the C-terminus helix3 is shortened. The absence of two residues in the active site of 90-MtCM corresponding to Ser84 and Gln88 of EcCM appears to be one reason for the low k(cat). Hence, 90-MtCM belongs to a subfamily of alpha-helical AroQ CMs termed AroQ(delta.) The CM gene (y2828) from Yersinia pestis encodes a 186 amino acid protein with an N-terminal signal peptide that directs the protein to the periplasm. The mature protein, \\*YpCM, exhibits Michaelis-Menten kinetics with a k(cat) of 70+/-5s(-1) and K(m) of 500+/-50microm at 37 degrees C and pH7.5. The 2.1A X-ray structure shows that \\*YpCM is an all alpha-helical protein, and functions as a homodimer, and that each protomer has an independent catalytic unit (Protein Data Bank ID: 2GBB). \\*YpCM belongs to the AroQ(gamma) class of CMs, and is similar to the secreted CM (Rv1885c, \\*MtCM) from M.tuberculosis.\n\n[PubMed Disclaimer](/disclaimer/)\n\n## Publication types\n\n-   Comparative Study\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Comparative+Study%22%5Bpt%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Comparative+Study)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n\n## MeSH terms\n\n-   Chorismate Mutase / chemistry\\*\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Chorismate+Mutase%2Fchemistry%22%5BMAJR%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Chorismate+Mutase)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Chorismate Mutase / classification\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Chorismate+Mutase%2Fclassification%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Chorismate+Mutase)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Chorismate Mutase / metabolism\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Chorismate+Mutase%2Fmetabolism%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Chorismate+Mutase)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Cloning, Molecular\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Cloning%2C+Molecular%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Cloning%2C+Molecular)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Crystallization\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Crystallization%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Crystallization)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Crystallography, X-Ray\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Crystallography%2C+X-Ray%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search