{"type":"text","timestamp":1778432340022,"sessionID":"ses_1ed339b18ffe5kTmxqWqbpAn8A","part":{"id":"prt_e12d3ed61001GioqCTu6VXs5W2","messageID":"msg_e12d3e930001F9ArCbKbwDIdy8","sessionID":"ses_1ed339b18ffe5kTmxqWqbpAn8A","type":"text","text":"I’m documenting the local research/design rationale, then I’ll obsolete the term with `consider` references rather than a direct replacement because the old term corresponds to a combined/superpathway concept.","time":{"start":1778432339297,"end":1778432340021},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_08933985f6498f8a016a00b95342d48193b26ef1d5b61cf383","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778432356422,"sessionID":"ses_1ed339b18ffe5kTmxqWqbpAn8A","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_TnE1m92959Wb9RLsrvx5ljeS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: RESEARCH.md\n+# Research Notes For Issue 32005\n+\n+## Summary\n+\n+GO:0009095 `aromatic amino acid biosynthetic process, prephenate pathway` corresponds to MetaCyc:PWY-3481, described in the issue as a superpathway combining L-phenylalanine biosynthesis II (MetaCyc:PWY-3462) and L-tyrosine biosynthesis II (MetaCyc:PWY-3461). The corresponding GO terms already carry these pathway-specific MetaCyc mappings as narrow matches:\n+\n+- GO:0009094 `L-phenylalanine biosynthetic process` has `xref: MetaCyc:PWY-3462 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}`.\n+- GO:0006571 `L-tyrosine biosynthetic process` has `xref: MetaCyc:PWY-3461 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}`.\n+\n+This supports obsoleting GO:0009095 as a combined/pre-composed pathway term and using `consider` references to the two separate biosynthetic process terms rather than a single `replaced_by` target.\n+\n+## Annotation Evidence Noted In Issue\n+\n+The issue reports four EXP annotations and recommends annotation review actions:\n+\n+- PMID:21102469: two UniProt annotations to Arabidopsis PAT and Petunia PPA-AT. The issue notes Petunia PPA-AT evidence supports L-phenylalanine biosynthesis and suggests moving that annotation to GO:0009094, while removing the Arabidopsis PAT BP annotation if no BP support is found.\n+- PMID:20883697: one TAIR annotation to Arabidopsis PAT. The issue describes this as biochemical evidence without BP support and recommends removal.\n+- PMID:18727669: one MTBBASE annotation to M. tuberculosis Rv0948c chorismate mutase. The issue describes this as biochemical/structural evidence without BP support and recommends removal.\n+\n+I attempted to verify direct annotations via `runoak -i amigo: associations GO:0009095`, but local `runoak` fails to start because of a dependency error (`AttributeError: type object 'Format' has no attribute 'JSON'`).\n+\n+## PMID Checks\n+\n+### PMID:21102469 \"Prephenate aminotransferase directs plant phenylalanine biosynthesis via arogenate\"\n+\n+PubMed verifies PMID:21102469 and reports the abstract statement: \"Biochemical and genetic characterization of enzymes showed that PPA-AT directs carbon flux from prephenate toward arogenate, making the arogenate pathway predominant in plant phenylalanine biosynthesis.\"\n+\n+Recommendation from issue is consistent with using GO:0009094 for the Petunia PPA-AT annotation if annotation review confirms the evidence.\n+\n+### PMID:20883697 \"Identification of a plant gene encoding glutamate/aspartate-prephenate aminotransferase: the last homeless enzyme of aromatic amino acids biosynthesis.\"\n+\n+`linkml-reference-validator cache reference PMID:20883697` succeeded and verified the title. The abstract describes purification, identification, and biochemical characterization of Arabidopsis thaliana prephenate aminotransferase activity, supporting the issue's characterization as biochemical rather than direct BP evidence.\n+\n+### PMID:18727669 \"A comparative biochemical and structural analysis of the intracellular chorismate mutase (Rv0948c) from Mycobacterium tuberculosis H(37)R(v) and the secreted chorismate mutase (y2828) from Yersinia pestis\"\n+\n+PubMed verifies PMID:18727669 and reports a biochemical/structural abstract focused on chorismate mutase activity, enzyme kinetics, and X-ray structures. This is consistent with the issue's recommendation that the BP annotation should be removed rather than migrated.\n+\n+## Tool Limitations\n+\n+- `runoak -i amigo: associations GO:0009095` failed locally due to the `runoak` dependency error above.\n+- `runoak -i ubergraph: usages GO:0009095` failed for the same reason.\n+- `linkml-reference-validator cache reference PMID:21102469` and `PMID:18727669` hit NCBI HTTP 429 rate limiting, so PubMed pages were checked via `webfetch` instead.\n*** Add File: DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+# Design Pattern Notes For Issue 32005\n+\n+## Relevant Pattern\n+\n+The target term is an existing biological process term using a biosynthetic-process logical definition:\n+\n+```obo\n+intersection_of: GO:0009058 ! biosynthetic process\n+intersection_of: has_intermediate CHEBI:57852 ! prephenate(2-)\n+intersection_of: has_primary_output CHEBI:33856 ! aromatic amino acid\n+```\n+\n+For obsoletion, these logical axioms must be removed. No new `intersection_of` axioms are being added.\n+\n+## Candidate Terms Checked\n+\n+GO:0009094 `L-phenylalanine biosynthetic process` is logically defined as a biosynthetic process with primary output CHEBI:58095 `L-phenylalanine zwitterion` and carries `xref: MetaCyc:PWY-3462 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}`.\n+\n+GO:0006571 `L-tyrosine biosynthetic process` is logically defined as a biosynthetic process with primary output CHEBI:58315 `L-tyrosine zwitterion` and carries `xref: MetaCyc:PWY-3461 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}`.\n+\n+These are appropriate `consider` targets because the obsolete term represented a combined pathway/superpathway rather than an exact match to either individual process.\n+\n+## Obsoletion Metadata Pattern\n+\n+Per GO obsoletion practice, the obsolete stanza should retain the historical id, namespace, obsolete-prefixed name, OBSOLETE-prefixed definition with original definition xrefs, obsoletion comment, term tracker item, `is_obsolete: true`, and `consider` references. It should not retain synonyms, xrefs, `is_a`, `relationship`, or `intersection_of` axioms.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA RESEARCH.md\nA DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,42 @@\n+# Research Notes For Issue 32005\n+\n+## Summary\n+\n+GO:0009095 `aromatic amino acid biosynthetic process, prephenate pathway` corresponds to MetaCyc:PWY-3481, described in the issue as a superpathway combining L-phenylalanine biosynthesis II (MetaCyc:PWY-3462) and L-tyrosine biosynthesis II (MetaCyc:PWY-3461). The corresponding GO terms already carry these pathway-specific MetaCyc mappings as narrow matches:\n+\n+- GO:0009094 `L-phenylalanine biosynthetic process` has `xref: MetaCyc:PWY-3462 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}`.\n+- GO:0006571 `L-tyrosine biosynthetic process` has `xref: MetaCyc:PWY-3461 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}`.\n+\n+This supports obsoleting GO:0009095 as a combined/pre-composed pathway term and using `consider` references to the two separate biosynthetic process terms rather than a single `replaced_by` target.\n+\n+## Annotation Evidence Noted In Issue\n+\n+The issue reports four EXP annotations and recommends annotation review actions:\n+\n+- PMID:21102469: two UniProt annotations to Arabidopsis PAT and Petunia PPA-AT. The issue notes Petunia PPA-AT evidence supports L-phenylalanine biosynthesis and suggests moving that annotation to GO:0009094, while removing the Arabidopsis PAT BP annotation if no BP support is found.\n+- PMID:20883697: one TAIR annotation to Arabidopsis PAT. The issue describes this as biochemical evidence without BP support and recommends removal.\n+- PMID:18727669: one MTBBASE annotation to M. tuberculosis Rv0948c chorismate mutase. The issue describes this as biochemical/structural evidence without BP support and recommends removal.\n+\n+I attempted to verify direct annotations via `runoak -i amigo: associations GO:0009095`, but local `runoak` fails to start because of a dependency error (`AttributeError: type object 'Format' has no attribute 'JSON'`).\n+\n+## PMID Checks\n+\n+### PMID:21102469 \"Prephenate aminotransferase directs plant phenylalanine biosynthesis via arogenate\"\n+\n+PubMed verifies PMID:21102469 and reports the abstract statement: \"Biochemical and genetic characterization of enzymes showed that PPA-AT directs carbon flux from prephenate toward arogenate, making the arogenate pathway predominant in plant phenylalanine biosynthesis.\"\n+\n+Recommendation from issue is consistent with using GO:0009094 for the Petunia PPA-AT annotation if annotation review confirms the evidence.\n+\n+### PMID:20883697 \"Identification of a plant gene encoding glutamate/aspartate-prephenate aminotransferase: the last homeless enzyme of aromatic amino acids biosynthesis.\"\n+\n+`linkml-reference-validator cache reference PMID:20883697` succeeded and verified the title. The abstract describes purification, identification, and biochemical characterization of Arabidopsis thaliana prephenate aminotransferase activity, supporting the issue's characterization as biochemical rather than direct BP evidence.\n+\n+### PMID:18727669 \"A comparative biochemical and structural analysis of the intracellular chorismate mutase (Rv0948c) from Mycobacterium tuberculosis H(37)R(v) and the secreted chorismate mutase (y2828) from Yersinia pestis\"\n+\n+PubMed verifies PMID:18727669 and reports a biochemical/structural abstract focused on chorismate mutase activity, enzyme kinetics, and X-ray structures. This is consistent with the issue's recommendation that the BP annotation should be removed rather than migrated.\n+\n+## Tool Limitations\n+\n+- `runoak -i amigo: associations GO:0009095` failed locally due to the `runoak` dependency error above.\n+- `runoak -i ubergraph: usages GO:0009095` failed for the same reason.\n+- `linkml-reference-validator cache reference PMID:21102469` and `PMID:18727669` hit NCBI HTTP 429 rate limiting, so PubMed pages were checked via `webfetch` instead.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,25 @@\n+# Design Pattern Notes For Issue 32005\n+\n+## Relevant Pattern\n+\n+The target term is an existing biological process term using a biosynthetic-process logical definition:\n+\n+```obo\n+intersection_of: GO:0009058 ! biosynthetic process\n+intersection_of: has_intermediate CHEBI:57852 ! prephenate(2-)\n+intersection_of: has_primary_output CHEBI:33856 ! aromatic amino acid\n+```\n+\n+For obsoletion, these logical axioms must be removed. No new `intersection_of` axioms are being added.\n+\n+## Candidate Terms Checked\n+\n+GO:0009094 `L-phenylalanine biosynthetic process` is logically defined as a biosynthetic process with primary output CHEBI:58095 `L-phenylalanine zwitterion` and carries `xref: MetaCyc:PWY-3462 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}`.\n+\n+GO:0006571 `L-tyrosine biosynthetic process` is logically defined as a biosynthetic process with primary output CHEBI:58315 `L-tyrosine zwitterion` and carries `xref: MetaCyc:PWY-3461 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}`.\n+\n+These are appropriate `consider` targets because the obsolete term represented a combined pathway/superpathway rather than an exact match to either individual process.\n+\n+## Obsoletion Metadata Pattern\n+\n+Per GO obsoletion practice, the obsolete stanza should retain the historical id, namespace, obsolete-prefixed name, OBSOLETE-prefixed definition with original definition xrefs, obsoletion comment, term tracker item, `is_obsolete: true`, and `consider` references. It should not retain synonyms, xrefs, `is_a`, `relationship`, or `intersection_of` axioms.\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md","relativePath":"RESEARCH.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,42 @@\n+# Research Notes For Issue 32005\n+\n+## Summary\n+\n+GO:0009095 `aromatic amino acid biosynthetic process, prephenate pathway` corresponds to MetaCyc:PWY-3481, described in the issue as a superpathway combining L-phenylalanine biosynthesis II (MetaCyc:PWY-3462) and L-tyrosine biosynthesis II (MetaCyc:PWY-3461). The corresponding GO terms already carry these pathway-specific MetaCyc mappings as narrow matches:\n+\n+- GO:0009094 `L-phenylalanine biosynthetic process` has `xref: MetaCyc:PWY-3462 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}`.\n+- GO:0006571 `L-tyrosine biosynthetic process` has `xref: MetaCyc:PWY-3461 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}`.\n+\n+This supports obsoleting GO:0009095 as a combined/pre-composed pathway term and using `consider` references to the two separate biosynthetic process terms rather than a single `replaced_by` target.\n+\n+## Annotation Evidence Noted In Issue\n+\n+The issue reports four EXP annotations and recommends annotation review actions:\n+\n+- PMID:21102469: two UniProt annotations to Arabidopsis PAT and Petunia PPA-AT. The issue notes Petunia PPA-AT evidence supports L-phenylalanine biosynthesis and suggests moving that annotation to GO:0009094, while removing the Arabidopsis PAT BP annotation if no BP support is found.\n+- PMID:20883697: one TAIR annotation to Arabidopsis PAT. The issue describes this as biochemical evidence without BP support and recommends removal.\n+- PMID:18727669: one MTBBASE annotation to M. tuberculosis Rv0948c chorismate mutase. The issue describes this as biochemical/structural evidence without BP support and recommends removal.\n+\n+I attempted to verify direct annotations via `runoak -i amigo: associations GO:0009095`, but local `runoak` fails to start because of a dependency error (`AttributeError: type object 'Format' has no attribute 'JSON'`).\n+\n+## PMID Checks\n+\n+### PMID:21102469 \"Prephenate aminotransferase directs plant phenylalanine biosynthesis via arogenate\"\n+\n+PubMed verifies PMID:21102469 and reports the abstract statement: \"Biochemical and genetic characterization of enzymes showed that PPA-AT directs carbon flux from prephenate toward arogenate, making the arogenate pathway predominant in plant phenylalanine biosynthesis.\"\n+\n+Recommendation from issue is consistent with using GO:0009094 for the Petunia PPA-AT annotation if annotation review confirms the evidence.\n+\n+### PMID:20883697 \"Identification of a plant gene encoding glutamate/aspartate-prephenate aminotransferase: the last homeless enzyme of aromatic amino acids biosynthesis.\"\n+\n+`linkml-reference-validator cache reference PMID:20883697` succeeded and verified the title. The abstract describes purification, identification, and biochemical characterization of Arabidopsis thaliana prephenate aminotransferase activity, supporting the issue's characterization as biochemical rather than direct BP evidence.\n+\n+### PMID:18727669 \"A comparative biochemical and structural analysis of the intracellular chorismate mutase (Rv0948c) from Mycobacterium tuberculosis H(37)R(v) and the secreted chorismate mutase (y2828) from Yersinia pestis\"\n+\n+PubMed verifies PMID:18727669 and reports a biochemical/structural abstract focused on chorismate mutase activity, enzyme kinetics, and X-ray structures. This is consistent with the issue's recommendation that the BP annotation should be removed rather than migrated.\n+\n+## Tool Limitations\n+\n+- `runoak -i amigo: associations GO:0009095` failed locally due to the `runoak` dependency error above.\n+- `runoak -i ubergraph: usages GO:0009095` failed for the same reason.\n+- `linkml-reference-validator cache reference PMID:21102469` and `PMID:18727669` hit NCBI HTTP 429 rate limiting, so PubMed pages were checked via `webfetch` instead.\n","additions":42,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","relativePath":"DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,25 @@\n+# Design Pattern Notes For Issue 32005\n+\n+## Relevant Pattern\n+\n+The target term is an existing biological process term using a biosynthetic-process logical definition:\n+\n+```obo\n+intersection_of: GO:0009058 ! biosynthetic process\n+intersection_of: has_intermediate CHEBI:57852 ! prephenate(2-)\n+intersection_of: has_primary_output CHEBI:33856 ! aromatic amino acid\n+```\n+\n+For obsoletion, these logical axioms must be removed. No new `intersection_of` axioms are being added.\n+\n+## Candidate Terms Checked\n+\n+GO:0009094 `L-phenylalanine biosynthetic process` is logically defined as a biosynthetic process with primary output CHEBI:58095 `L-phenylalanine zwitterion` and carries `xref: MetaCyc:PWY-3462 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}`.\n+\n+GO:0006571 `L-tyrosine biosynthetic process` is logically defined as a biosynthetic process with primary output CHEBI:58315 `L-tyrosine zwitterion` and carries `xref: MetaCyc:PWY-3461 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}`.\n+\n+These are appropriate `consider` targets because the obsolete term represented a combined pathway/superpathway rather than an exact match to either individual process.\n+\n+## Obsoletion Metadata Pattern\n+\n+Per GO obsoletion practice, the obsolete stanza should retain the historical id, namespace, obsolete-prefixed name, OBSOLETE-prefixed definition with original definition xrefs, obsoletion comment, term tracker item, `is_obsolete: true`, and `consider` references. It should not retain synonyms, xrefs, `is_a`, `relationship`, or `intersection_of` axioms.\n","additions":25,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA RESEARCH.md\nA DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","time":{"start":1778432356416,"end":1778432356421}},"metadata":{"